    <h3>[cCc] Web Tracking</h3>
    
    <h4>[cCc] Log Files</h4>
    <p>PlaceCal.org follows a standard procedure of using log files. These files log visitors when they visit websites. All hosting companies do this and a part of hosting services’ analytics. The information collected by log files include internet protocol (IP) addresses, browser type, Internet Service Provider (ISP), date and time stamp, referring/exit pages, and possibly the number of clicks. These are not linked to any information that is personally identifiable. The purpose of the information is for analysing trends, administering the site, tracking users’ movement on the website, and gathering demographic information.</p>
      
    <h4>[cCc] Cookies and Web Beacons</h4>
    <p>Like any other website, PlaceCal.org uses ‘cookies’. These cookies are used to store information including visitors’ preferences, and the pages on the website that the visitor accessed or visited. The information is used to optimize the users’ experience by customizing our web page content based on visitors’ browser type and/or other information.</p>
    
    <h4>[cCc] Third Party Privacy Policies</h4>
    <p>PlaceCal’s Privacy Policy does not apply to Plausible, which we use to track visits. You should therefore consult Plausible’s Privacy Policies for more detailed information. </p>
    <p>Plausible's Data Policy can be found here: <a href="https://plausible.io/data-policy" target="_blank">https://plausible.io/data-policy</a>.</p>
    <p>Plausible does not use Cookies to track your data. Nevertheless, you may choose to disable cookies through your individual browser options. If you would like to know more detailed information about cookie management on specific web browsers, please consult the website for that browser.</p>

